<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>McLaren have given fans their take on what the future looks like as they presented a futuristic race car that can take to the tracks in 2050. </p>

<p>McLaren Applied Technologies, the sister company of the Formula One team, worked extensively gathering opinions from fans of the sport and now present the 2050: the MCLExtreme which features an on-board artificial intelligence co-pilot, an electric battery that can be folded away and self-healing tyres. </p>

<p>The work done by MAT encapsulates more than just the race car for the drivers in three decades time. They have also extensively given their thoughts on developments in driver human performance, racing tracks of the future and the fan experience we can expect to see in 2050.</p>

<p>Scroll down for video </p>

<p>McLaren have unveiled to fans their exciting take on the future of Formula One in the form of the 2050: the MCLExtreme</p>

<p>The exciting and daring futuristic design features an on-board artificial intelligence co-pilot for drivers and self-healing tyres</p>

<p>Ruling out flying cars - even in 30 years time - McLaren instead focused on delivering the most advanced race car ever</p>

<p>Artificial intelligence is going to form a key part of technological advancement in the sport moving forward in coming years</p>

<p>McLaren's research also looked at the tracks of the future and how the overall fan experience would go on to differ from now</p>

<p>Group of teens punch 74-year-old woman after stealing her purse</p>

<p>Kaitlyn Bristowe says she cried following mean 'DWTS' comments</p>

<p>Diversity perform powerful dance about police brutality and racism</p>

<p>Trailer for Nickelodeon children's show Made by Maddie</p>

